  "description": [
    "Kennedy Temporarily Escaped The Shackles Of The ADA Krause Candidate For Congress Tells About Fumbling Of Cuban Problem A candidate for Congress in St Louis charges that President Kennedy has tem porarily escaped from the shackles of his ADA advisers and credits his second change of policy on Cuba to the infor mation he received from the people while he was out making campaign speeches He cited the fact that prior to his election as President that Kennedy stated The United States will not tol erate a Communist regime ninety miles from our shores This candidate is J Marvin Krause a Republican candidate for Congress in the Third Congressional District of Mis souri Krause blames this change of policy on the part of Kennedy on his advisers from the Americans for Democratic Ac tion Kennedys Failure Heres what he said The administrations failure to take positive action at the proper time against Castro advised the entire world that his ADA advisors in the last 20 months have caused the President to make a complete reversal of his undoubtedly sincere feeling he had before he started keeping company with them Continuing Krause said As President after he had been caught in"
